Sentencas: A brazing process for the fuel electrode (anode) contacting of a micro-tubular fuel cell is reported.
Titulo: Development of a novel electroless deposited nickel braze for micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell current collector contacting

Sentencas: The low-cost, novel, electroless deposited braze suitable for mass production was optimised with respect to material loading and brazing environment.
Titulo: Development of a novel electroless deposited nickel braze for micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell current collector contacting

Sentencas: Durable current collector-anode joints were obtained while protecting sensitive solid oxide fuel cell components.
Titulo: Development of a novel electroless deposited nickel braze for micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell current collector contacting

Sentencas: It was determined that a minimum braze loading of 20 mu m thickness was required to join the current collector at multiple contacts along the interior tube wall.
Titulo: Development of a novel electroless deposited nickel braze for micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell current collector contacting

Sentencas: The final brazed current collector design achieved a high peak power density of 0.14 W.cm(-2) at 750 degrees C, 2.35 times higher than for the un-brazed design.
Titulo: Development of a novel electroless deposited nickel braze for micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell current collector contacting
